coref: A Dog had learned to carry A Dog master's dinner to A Dog every day. A Dog was very faithful to A Dog duty, though the smell of the good things in the basket tempted A Dog. The Dogs in the neighborhood noticed A Dog carrying the basket and soon discovered what was in the basket. The Dogs in the neighborhood made several attempts to steal the basket from A Dog. But A Dog always guarded the basket faithfully. Then one day all the Dogs in the neighborhood got together and met A Dog on A Dog way with the basket. A Dog A Dog tried to run away from all the Dogs in the neighborhood. But at last A Dog stopped to argue. That was A Dog mistake. all the Dogs in the neighborhood soon made A Dog feel so ridiculous that A Dog dropped the basket and seized a large piece of roast meat intended for his master's dinner. Very well, A Dog said, you divide the rest.
